***************************************************************************
*  MIPS_SystemC                                                           *
*  MIPS Model in SystemC with a Graphical User Interface                  *
*  Arquitectura de Computadores II - Universidade de Aveiro - 2007        *
***************************************************************************

### Information

   MIPS_SystemC builds a SystemC model of the MIPS architecture. 
   The architecture is similar to the one described in Henessy&Patterson92. 
   It includes a graphical user interface that uses Qt libraries.

### Version Info

    MIPS_SystemC v0.6.4 (Beta Release) - 16 October, 2007

### Contents

    README                    This README File
    MIPS_SystemC              precompiled simulator using shared libs
    *.cpp *.h                 SystemC MIPS model
    GUI/*.cpp GUI/*.h         User Interface source files
    refman.pdf                Documentation

### Operating System and Compiler

    The binaries were compiled with gcc/g++ - Gnu Project C/C++ Compiler
    (gcc version 2.95.3 19991030 prerelease) using the Qt libraries 
    (release 2.2.4) on Mandrake Linux 7.2, release 2.2.17-21mdk.
	
    It is required to have the Qt libraries release 2.2.4 (or later) 
    installed in the system prior to compilation. 

    It is required to have the SystemC release 2.0.1 
    installed in the system prior to compilation.

    More information on Qt can be found at http://www.trolltech.com
    More information on SystemC can be found at http://www.systemc.org

### Instructions 

    1- define QTDIR:

         for example:
         export QTDIR=/usr/lib/qt2
	
    2- define SYSTEMC:

         for example:
         export SYSTEMC=/usr/local/systemc-2.0.1

    3- compile:

         make

    4- run 

         MIPS_SystemC


